    Scope and Contents
SHAWNEETOWN BANK PROJECT
Sherman, resident of Shawneetown, recalls the Shawneetown Bank: bank lobby, furnishings, marble counters, and ironwork, as well as individual tellers and cashiers. She also recalls the bank's apartments: layout of rooms and furnishings, the coal furnace, kitchen, bedrooms, tenants, the second and third floors, and the 1937 flood.1 tape, 90 mins., 42 pp.
Interview by Horace Waggoner, 1978
